  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop your<strong> potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 18-20 min</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1636108881523-x200.jpeg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1636108881523-x400.jpeg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1636108881523-x700.jpeg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1636108881523-x1000.jpeg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1636108881523-x1500.jpeg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Pat your <strong>cod fillet[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Sprinkle 2/3 of your <strong>curry powder </strong>(save the rest for later!) over the fish and rub it into both sides until evenly coated</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and set aside – these are your <strong>curried cod fillet[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1636109012744-x200.jpeg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1636109012744-x400.jpeg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1636109012744-x700.jpeg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1636109012744-x1000.jpeg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1636109012744-x1500.jpeg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s] </strong>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1636109386178-x200.jpeg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1636109386178-x400.jpeg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1636109386178-x700.jpeg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1636109386178-x1000.jpeg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1636109386178-x1500.jpeg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes have had an initial 18-20 min, add the <strong>pepper strips</strong> and <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> to the tray[s]</p><p>Sprinkle over the <strong>remaining curry powder</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1636109392552-x200.jpeg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1636109392552-x400.jpeg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1636109392552-x700.jpeg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1636109392552-x1000.jpeg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1636109392552-x1500.jpeg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Place the <strong>curried cod fillet[s]</strong> on top of the veg</p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven and increase the heat to 240ºC/ 220ºC (fan)/ gas 9 for a further 12 min or until the fish is cooked through, the potatoes are crisp and the vegetables have softened – this is your <strong>one tray curried cod bake</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1636109397092-x200.jpeg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1636109397092-x400.jpeg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1636109397092-x700.jpeg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1636109397092-x1000.jpeg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1636109397092-x1500.jpeg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst everything is cooking, combine your <strong>natural yoghurt</strong> with your<strong> ground turmeric</strong>, a small splash of <strong>cold water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a small bowl – this is your <strong>turmeric yoghurt</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
